g.text: From the main menu, navigate to DOWNLOAD, then
Enter the password, then select Automatic Model Selection.
The password can be found on TriumphOnline.
Click Start. Is the model detected correctly?
Is the current calibration up to date?
Refer to the calibration report on TriumphOnline.
Select the correct calibration for your instrument units (MPH or
Check the selected calibration is correct for your model and
instrument units (MPH or km/h). Click Confirm.
The diagnostic software will prompt you to check that the
engine stop switch is in the STOP (OFF) position.
The download process will automatically progress when the
diagnostic software detects that the engine stop switch is in the
STOP (OFF) position and the engine ECM is powered down.
Allow the download to complete. This should take
Click Finish when the download has completed.
Switch the engine Start/Stop switch to the STOP (OFF)
The diagnostic software will prompt you to check that the ABS
Check the ABS fuse is removed. Click Next.
Check all ECMs for stored DTCs and erase as neccesary.
